@516  = ~That is one of the best childhoods a person could have. Did you like Candlekeep?~
@517  = ~Very much. It was a small community, so everyone knew everyone else, and it was very friendly. And I loved the library.~
@518  = ~I did. It was a good place to grow up.~
@519  = ~No, it was a bore. It was a small town with nothing to do. I'm glad to be out of there.~
@520  = ~That does sound appealing. The town where I grew up was small, too, but they did not have that library. I did not learn to read at all until I joined the temple, but I enjoy it now.~
@521  = ~But come, let us catch up. We'll have time to talk as we travel, I imagine.~
